=== Cultural assets ===

=== Important cultural property ===
*7 wooden statues of gods<ref group="Note">The history of this item's designation as a cultural property is as follows.
*In 1901 (Meiji 34), the following three buildings (total of eight buildings) were designated as important cultural properties (formerly national treasures). (Ministry of Home Affairs Notification No. 20, March 27, 1909)
**Three wooden statues of the gods (Seated statue of Yamatobi Hyakusho Hime no Mikoto, Seated statue of Wakoku Kahime no Mikoto, and Seated statue of Owa Nekohikotaikion no Mikoto)
**1 wooden seated male god statue
**4 wooden seated goddess statues
*Of the ``Three Wooden God Statues'', the Watatsubi Hyakusho Hime no Mikoto statue was purchased by the Agency for Cultural Affairs in 2017 after its whereabouts were unknown for a while.
*In 2020 (Reiwa 2), the ``Three Wooden God Statues'' were divided into two: ``Seated Statue of Watanbi Hyakusho Hime no Mikoto'' (Kept by the Agency for Cultural Affairs) and ``Seated Statue of Wakoku Kaohime no Mikoto/Owa Nekohiko Taisho Hime no Mikoto'' (Owned by Mizunushi Shrine). The latter was combined with two previously designated Important Cultural Properties (``1 Wooden Seated Statue of a Male God'' and ``4 Wooden Seated Statues of a Goddess'') and was designated as an Important Cultural Property under the name ``7 Wooden God Statues''. (Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology Notification No. 120, September 30, 2020)</ref>
*Pair of wooden guardian dogs
*Raimon Radenkura
*{{ill|lt=Great Prajnaparamita Sutra|Q15905785|qid=Q15905785|lt=Great Prajnaparamita Sutra|1=Large Prajñāpāramitā Sūtras}} 600 chapters included: 60 sutra boxes, inner bottom sutra box promotion record, etc. in ink

Authority: For properties designated up to 2000, refer to "National Treasures and Important Cultural Properties, Special Volume," Comprehensive Catalog by Owner, Comprehensive Name Index, and Statistical Materials (Mainichi Shimbun, 2000). Changes since 2001 are noted separately.

